properties.abstract: A different kind of lake tour: this pleasant excursion circles the Heidsee lake not along its shores, but high above on trails and small roads. Most of the ascents are made by means of mountain railways, so you can enjoy the view of the Heidsee lake and the Lenzerheide valley even more.
properties.description:
Runda Lai is not a lake tour in the classic sense. All the trails around the lake are single trails and - with the help of cable cars and gondolas  at an altitude between 2000 meters and the lake level. From Lenzerheide, the route leads east of the Heidsee directly to the Rothorn cable car which provides an easy 500-metre altitude gain. 

From the Scharmoin middle station, named after the alp, the route climbs gently uphill over the Ochsenlpli up to 2000 metres - the starting point for the first descent. The hard-surfaced panoramic trail leads past alpine pastures, flowering meadows and a few forest passages. 

Back down in Churwalden, the gondola takes the bikers back up to Heidbel. The view of the Rothorn's eastern flank and of Lenzerheide is magnificent. During the rest of the ride the valley and the lake are almost always visible. An exciting mix of Alpine roads and single trails leads from Sttzertli via Spoina directly to the lake and back to the starting point.
